<HEADLINE> OAU, Ethiopia Support One-China Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Organization of African Unity
(OAU) Secretary General Salim Ahmed Salem said here Friday that
the OAU always supports the "One-China" policy upheld by the
Chinese government.
</P>
<P>
"We also appreciate the 'One country, two systems policy' put
forward by the Chinese government," the OAU chief told Chinese
ambassador Jiang Zhengyun in an interview here, a source from the
Chinese Embassy told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
The OAU fully understands China's concern about its national
sovereignty and territorial integrity. This is also the stand
taken by the majority of African countries, Salim added.
</P>
<P>
Salim made the remarks when referring to claims by Lee Teng-hui
of Taiwan who described cross-Straits relations between China and
Taiwan as "relations between state and state. "
</P>
<P>
Taiwan as a province of China is an inalienable part of the
territory of the People's Republic of China, said the OAU chief.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, Ethiopia also reiterated that Taiwan is part of
China.
</P>
<P>
In his meeting with Chinese ambassador Jiang Zhengyun,
Ethiopian Deputy Foreign Minister Tekeda Alemu said that the
Ethiopian government has been maintaining the "One -China" policy
on the basis of the good relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Referring to Lee Teng-hui's "two-states theory", Tekeda said
that the Taiwan authorities is playing a game which is at once
dangerous and unrealistic. 
</P>
</TEXT>
