<HEADLINE> OAU Donates $200,000 for Sierra Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Speaking at a ceremony at the OAU headquarters here, Secretary
General Salim Ahmed Salim said that the donation is showing OAU's
concerns about the many thousands of Sierra Leoneans severely
affected by the civil war in the west African country.
</P>
<P>
An OAU press release issued here quoted the OAU chief as saying
that "the peace agreement signed between the parties to the Sierra
Leonean conflict in Lome, Togo on July 7, 1997 had also made
provision for international humanitarian assistance to be
delivered to Sierra Leone."
</P>
<P>
Salim stated that the OAU was considering ways and means for
more concrete assistance to the implementation of the agreement.
</P>
<P>
Sierra Leonean ambassador to OAU Ibrahm Kamara expressed the
extreme gratitude of the government and people of Sierra Leone for
the gesture of the OAU which he described as a "commendable" act
which would help thousands of people in distress.
</P>
<P>
He said the OAU had remained steadfast in its efforts to
promote the peace process since 1995 and particularly the OAU was
the first international organization who had come out to condemn
the coup d'etat of May 1997 in Freetown. 
</P>
</TEXT>
