<HEADLINE> SADC Ministers Adopt Resolutions on Local </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Ministers of local government
from the Southern African Development Community (SADC) members
have resolved to cooperate on policy initiatives and projects that
seek to deliver basic services and infrastructure especially to
the poor.
</P>
<P>
The resolutions were adopted Friday at the end of a three-day
SADC conference on local government held in Johannesburg, South
Africa.
</P>
<P>
The ministers have also resolved to cooperate on policy
initiatives and projects that will create an environment suitable
for increased municipal partnerships with other key role players
in service delivery and development.
</P>
<P>
Integrated planning to minimize environmental degradation to
enable the region to deal effectively with natural disasters was
another key area the ministers agreed upon.
</P>
<P>
On regional cooperation, information sharing and capacity
building, the SADC local government ministers recognized the need
to cooperate and have therefore resolved to support the formation
of a national associations of local government in countries where
such organizations do not exist.
</P>
<P>
This would be done to promote networking and communication
between local authorities and to enable them to speak with one
voice.
</P>
<P>
Another critical component area of agreement was the
establishment of local government forum within the SADC.
</P>
<P>
They also agreed that such a forum should include an annual
conference to enable the continued sharing of ideas and
cooperation on local government matters.
</P>
<P>
A ministerial task team consisting of South Africa, Mozambique,
Zambia and Zimbabwe was established to investigate and recommend a
modus operandi, institutional structure and terms of reference for
the forum. 
</P>
</TEXT>
