<HEADLINE> Sovereignty of Afghanistan Must be Respected: Pak </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan Minister of State for
Foreign Affairs Siddique Khan Kanju Friday said that Afghanistan
is an independent sovereign state and its sovereignty should be
respected.
</P>
<P>
Talking to reporters here, Kanju said Pakistan fully respects
the sovereignty of Afghanistan, reiterating that Pakistan will not
allow its territory to be used against any other sovereign state.
</P>
<P>
"To us Afghanistan is a sovereign country and its sovereignty
has to be respected. We share a long border with the land-locked
country and whatever happens there inevitably affects us," Kanju
added.
</P>
<P>
In August last year, the United States launched a missile
attack targeting Osama's hideouts in the Afghan city of Khost but
failed to cause any major damage to the millionaire who was
accused of masterminding the bombings at U.S. embassies in Kenya
and Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
Many people believe the United States is planning a fresh
attack on Osama as the ruling Afghan Taliban rejected again its
latest requirement to extradite the alleged terrorist. 
</P>
