<HEADLINE> France, Portugal Agree on Defense Cooperation in Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 30 (Xinhua) -- France and Portugal signed Friday an
agreement on carrying out defense cooperation, especially in
Africa, announced the French Defense Ministry.
</P>
<P>
French Defense Minister Alain Richard and his Portuguese
counterpart, Jaime Gama, signed the agreement here, which focuses
on Franco-Portuguese cooperation in solving crises in Africa.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, France will invite Portugal to join the
French-sponsored concept of Reinforcement of African Capacities in
Peace Keeping and implement common defense actions in Africa.
</P>
<P>
Portugal, which will exercise the rotating presidency of
European Union (EU) in the early half of 2,000, will organize with
the Organization of African Unity an EU-African summit during its
EU presidency.
</P>
<P>
French oil groups Elf and Total have made great investment in
the oil resources of Angola, which is a Portuguese speaking
country, and is interested in developing cooperation with another
Portuguese speaking country, Mozambique.
</P>
<P>
French President Jacques Chirac visited the two countries last
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
