<HEADLINE> Tanzania Satisfied with Ties With China: Officer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania is satisfied with
its friendly relationship with China not only in the military
field but also in political and economic sectors, a high-ranking
Tanzanian officer said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Chief of Tanzania People's Defense Force, General Robert Mboma,
 described these bilateral ties as "sincere" when attending a
reception in the Chinese embassy here in celebration of the 72th
anniversary of the founding of the Chinese People's Liberation
Army (PLA).
</P>
<P>
"We will not forget China's assistance," Mboma said. "People in
Dar es Salaam and other parts of Tanzania would say the friendship
demonstrated by China has been sincere."
</P>
<P>
Mboma said many Tanzanian army men, including himself, received
training in China.
</P>
<P>
The Charge d'affaires of the Chinese embassy, Liu Youfa, who
hosted the reception, said the ties between the armed forces of
the China and Tanzania is an important part of the friendly
relationship between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Liu said in the past decades, the Chinese PLA has been
dedicated to developing its relationship with the armed forces of
other states, especially developing countries, on the basis of
peaceful co-existence.
</P>
<P>
He said Tanzania's Minister of Defense and National Service
Edgar Maokola-Majogo will visit China at the end of this year. The
visit, he said, will strongly push the friendship between China
and Tanzania to a new level. 
</P>
</TEXT>
