<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ghana Gold Mines Lose 63,000 Ounces of Gold for </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Ashanti Goldfields Company (AGC)
Group, one of the leading gold producers in the world, lost
approximately 63,000 ounces of gold at the Obuasi mine during the
industrial action by workers last May, an AGC report said Friday.
</P>
<P>
 However, operations have normalized and officials of the
company said production levels are set to improve gradually,
saying: "about half of the Obuasi production shortfall was offset
by 30,000 ounces better than the forecast production at the
Bibiani, Siguiri and Iduapriem mines," all owned by Ashanti.
</P>
<P>
 Total gold production for the second quarter stood at 744,772
ounces, which was below the forecast performance, compared with
705,875 ounces produced in the first quarter of 1998, the Ghana
News Agency (GNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
 Statistics in the second quarter report of AGC said the
company, however, registered a six percent increase in its
earnings, making 16.4 million dollars compared to the 15.5
million dollars realized during the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
 Turnover for the first six months of the company was 284.1
million dollars compared with the 277.3 million dollars in the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
 The report said Ashanti has concluded an agreement with the
Ghana Mine workers' Union and Ministry of Employment and Social
Welfare that will make Ashanti reduce its work force by more than
2,000.
</P>
<P>
 The retrenchment, the report noted, has been accepted by the
Obuasi work force, and will be enforced over six months' period
from September 1, this year.
</P>
<P>
 The plan is to reduce Obuasi's operating cost by about seven
million dollars, a figure, equivalent to nine dollars per ounce at
current production levels.
</P>
<P>
 The report said Ashanti has increased its level of hedging
protection to 11 million ounces. Fifty percent of reserves are now
hedged at an average price of 389 dollars per ounce, protecting
the group against the current difficult gold market.
</P>
<P>
The first gold production will be on target in the second half
of 2000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
