<HEADLINE> Zhupina Wins Women's Platform Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISTANBUL, July 31 (Xinhua) -- World champion Elena Zhupina of
Ukraine won her second diving gold at the European championships
on Saturday after beating Dolores Saez de Ibarra in the final.
</P>
<P>
Zhupina, who won the three-metre springboard synchronised title
with Anna Sorokina on Thursday, took the lead from Svetlana
Timoshinina of Russia in the penultimate and fourth round after
the Timoshinina lost points for a poor entry.
</P>
<P>
But Saez de Ibarra produced a superb final round dive with a
back two and a half somersaults and half twist. The dive gave her
78.30 points, the highest score of the final.
</P>
<P>
Zhupina felt the pressure but still put up a good dive, earning
73.92 points from a back one and a half somersaults with 3 and a
half twists.
</P>
<P>
Zhupina won the gold with a total of 338.28 points. Saez de
Ibarra took silver on 329.22 and Timoshinina took the bronze at
307.53. 
</P>
