<DOCNO> XIE19990731.0086 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tianjin Hit by Heat Wave </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The port city of Tianjin in north
China has been sweltering under a heat wave since mid July.
</P>
<P>
On July 24, the daily temperature in the Tianjin urban area
reached a record 39.5 degrees centigrade, and was as high as 40
degrees in some outlying areas.
</P>
<P>
This long heat spell is the result of a high pressure warm air
mass that has been hovering over northern China, according to
meteorologists.
</P>
<P>
Many people were forced to stay at their air-conditioned homes
or go to parks and swimming pools to escape the heat, and sales of
electric fans and air conditioners are brisk in the city.
</P>
<P>
Meteorologists are urging residents to drink more water and eat
more fruit and vegetables to avoid heatstroke. 
</P>
</TEXT>
