<HEADLINE> Section of Key State Expressway Opens to Traffic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, July 31 (Xinhua) -- A section of an expressway
linking Beijing and Shenyang, capital of northeast China's
Liaoning Province, opened to traffic today on a trial basis.
</P>
<P>
The 167-km-long section begins at Yutian County and ends in the
city of Qinhuangdao in north China's Hebei Province. This section
is a major component of the 199-km-long Baodi-Shanhaiguan section
of the Beijing-Shenyang expressway, a key State projects.
</P>
<P>
The Baodi-Shanhaiguan section involved a total investment of 5.
6 billion yuan (672 million U.S. dollars), including 220 million U.
S. dollars from the Asian Development Bank. The section extends
from the border between Baodi County in the port city of Tianjin
and Yutian County in Hebei to Qinhuangdao.
</P>
<P>
The Yutian-Qinhuangdao section opened to traffic six months
ahead of schedule in a bid to promote the development of the local
tourism industry and economic cooperation between northeast and
north China. Along the expressway are such scenic spots as
Beidaihe, a famous summer resort, and Qingdongling, the Eastern
Tombs of the Qing Dynasty (1644-1911).
</P>
<P>
Construction of the Baodi-Shanhaiguan section began in 1996 and
is near completion.
</P>
<P>
Thus far, Hebei has opened eight expressways with a total
length of 843 km. By the end of the year, Hebei's highways are
expected to extend to 1,460 km. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
