<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Possible Cause of Detonator Explosion Found </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The mixed transportation of two
contraindicated detonators might be the cause of the explosion in
Changshou County, Chongqing Municipality in southwest China, which
killed 14 and seriously injured 18 others on July 27.
</P>
<P>
After an investigation, experts from the public security
departments of Chongqing Municipality, neighboring Yunnan Province,
and the government of Changshou County believe the truck may have
violated State regulations on the transportation of explosives by
carrying 285 kg of two contraindicated detonators.
</P>
<P>
Also, the boxes containing the detonators were not tightly
secured during transportation. A possible collision of the two
detonators in the course of transportation may have caused the
explosion.
</P>
<P>
Experts have ruled out the possibility that the explosion was
caused by any individual.
</P>
<P>
The truck started out from Yunnan Province, and suddenly
exploded as it passed the residential area of Fengcheng Township
in Changshou County. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
