<HEADLINE> Defense Minister: PLA to be Leaner, Stronger with Chinese Characteristics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister Chi
Haotian stressed here today that "we should do everything within
the framework of the overall military strategy for the new
historical period and unswervingly take the road of building a
leaner but stronger army with Chinese characteristics."
</P>
<P>
Chi, also a member of the Political Bureau of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, vice-chairman of the
Central Military Commission, and state councilor, made the remarks
during a reception today marking the 72nd founding anniversary of
the Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA).
</P>
<P>
