through science and technology and enhance its combat
effectiveness by relying upon scientific and technological
progress," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We should keep up with the trends in military development in
the world, more vigorously carry out studies on military theories
suited to Chinese conditions, strengthen defense-related
scientific and technological research, and gradually upgrade our
weaponry and equipment," he added.
</P>
<P>
Chi reiterated the hope that efforts should be made to "
effectively strengthen the PLA's defense capabilities and combat
effectiveness in war with modern technologies, especially for hi-
tech wars."
</P>
<P>
When it comes to the training of military personnel, Chi
emphasized that "a contingent of new-type, well-educated, and well-
disciplined military personnel" should be brought up to "lay a
solid foundation for building the PLA in the next century."
</P>
<P>
Chi also said that the PLA should intensify efforts to make
itself politically and ideologically sound, and should "keep to
its nature, purpose, and inherent quality."
</P>
<P>
"We will continue to be strict with the army, and run the army
in accordance with law, so as to build a more regular army," he
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
