<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Defense Minister Reviews Last Year's Army Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese People's Liberation
Army (PLA) successfully approached its goal of downsizing the army
by 500,000 last year, according to Chinese Defense Minister Chi
Haotian today.
</P>
<P>
Chi, also a member of the Political Bureau of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, vice chairman of the
Central Military Commission, and state councilor, made the remarks
during a reception today marking the 72nd founding anniversary of
the PLA.
</P>
<P>
"The PLA is reorganizing and restructuring itself in phases in
a planned manner with the main objective of downsizing the army by
500,000, which will be another step forward toward developing 'a
leaner but stronger and more efficient' composite force," said Chi.
</P>
<P>
Chi added that the PLA has made progress in "building a
revolutionary, modernized, and regular army" in line with the
general requirements of "political soundness and military
competence, a fine style of work, strict discipline, and adequate
logistic support" as put forward by Chinese President Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
On the PLA's implementation of the decision to disengage the
PLA and the Armed Police forces from business activities, Chi
pointed out that "the PLA has promptly shut down its commercial
enterprises and handed them over to local authorities."
</P>
<P>
The PLA's victory over last summer's devastating floods added
another glorious chapter to the history of the army, Chi said.
</P>
</TEXT>
