<HEADLINE> Defense Minister: PLA to Contribute to a New Security Concept </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Defense Minister Chi
Haotian said here today that the Chinese People's Liberation Army
(PLA) will contribute to "the gradual realization of a new
security concept featuring mutual trust, mutual benefit, and
equality and cooperation".
</P>
<P>
Chi, also a member of the Political Bureau of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, vice chairman of the
Central Military Commission, and state councilor, made the remarks
during a reception today marking the 72nd founding anniversary of
the PLA.
</P>
<P>
It is our sincere hope to establish and advance friendly
relations with all countries in the world on the basis of the Five
Principles of Peaceful Co-existence and vigorously conduct
exchanges and cooperation with armies of all other countries, so
as to "contribute to the establishment of a fair and rational new
international order," he said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of the international situation at the turn of the
century, Chi pointed out that hegemonism and power politics still
exist and have shown new manifestations, despite peace and
development remaining the main themes of the time.
</P>
<P>
"A salient feature is the pursuit of military interventionism
and the new 'gunboat policy,'" he indicated, adding that "we
should always be prepared for any possible danger even in times of
peace" and strengthen national defense.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
