<DOCNO> XIE19990731.0112 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Exposure of Li Hongzhi, a Serious Political Struggle (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The influential Chinese bimonthly
magazine Qiushi (Seeking Truth) said in its seventh special issue
that China's ongoing struggle against the Falun Gong organization
is an ideological and political struggle which has a bearing on
the fundamental faith of Communists.
</P>
<P>
Falun Dafa, or Falun Gong, disseminates idealism and theism,
negates all scientific truth, demands that practitioners act in
accordance with the doctrine of Li Hongzhi, and prohibits them
from following other theories, said a commentary in the bimonthly
published here today.
</P>
<P>
In other words, Falun Dafa forbids people from believing in any
scientific truth, including Marxism. This obviously violates China
's Constitution and poses a grave challenge to the fundamental
guiding ideology of the Communist Party of China (CPC) and the
government, it noted.
</P>
<P>
Facts have proven once again that if Marxism doesn't occupy the
ideological sphere, non-Marxism or anti-Marxism will be bound to
seize it. So long as one fails to grasp Marxist scientific outlook
and methodology, it is impossible for one to have firm ideals and
faith, distinguish right from wrong, the beautiful from the ugly,
or the benevolent from the evil, and then one is bound to deviate
from the principle of Party spirit, the commentary said.
</P>
<P>
It is clear that Falun Gong has attained its goal of
infiltrating the minds of some Party members and cadres by taking
advantage of a lack of political sensitivity to transform their
world outlook. When they start practicing Falun Gong, their ideals
and faith will waver, and they will deviate from Marxism and Party
principles.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
