<HEADLINE> East China Province Starts Building Major Expressway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Construction began Friday on a
293-km expressway linking the capital of east China's Zhejiang
Province, Hangzhou, with a dozen cities and counties in the
central and western regions of the coastal province.
</P>
<P>
The expressway will be completed at an estimated cost of 8.6
billion yuan, of which 2.08 billion yuan is in loans from the
Japanese government. The new expressway will allow motorists to
travel at speeds between 100-120 kilometers per hour.
</P>
<P>
The project, which will include 20 cloverleaves, is scheduled
for completion in four years. The expressway will be part of a
national highway from Shanghai in the east to Yunnan Province in
the southwest.
</P>
<P>
When the project is complete, the province's expressway system
will be 1,000-km long, and drive time from Hangzhou to other major
cities in the province will be shortened by as much as four hours.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
