<P>
-- France and some other European countries have expressed
reservation over the "Pact of Stability for Southeast Europe,"
which was initiated by Germany and aimed at integrating all
central and eastern European nations -- including Ukraine -- to
the European Union, because EU lacks a specific policy toward
eastern Europe and a strategy to absorb the east European
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
