<HEADLINE> Djibouti-Eritrea Border Closed: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Djibouti has closed its border
with Eritrea following an exchange of fire last Saturday between a
terrorist group and the Djibouti Security Forces along the border,
the Ethiopian Herald newspaper reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Unidentified Djibouti officials were quoted as saying that
about 100 terrorists launched attacks in the Doha area of the
Djiboutian territory.
</P>
<P>
The armed terrorists were said to have infiltrated in Djibouti
from Assab through its common border with Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-seven terrorists were killed, four wounded and five
others captured in the exchange of fire that lasted for an hour,
the officials said.
</P>
<P>
Following the incident, Djibouti has since last Monday ordered
the closure of its borders with Eritrea, they added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
