<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNHCR Repatriates 1,474 Ethiopian Refugees From </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations High
Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) has concluded the repatriation
of 1,474 refugees from camps in northern Kenya to Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
The last plane load of 55 Ethiopian refugees left Kenya Friday,
the East African Standard newspaper reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 21-flight repatriation of the Ethiopians began on July 15
and was completed Friday, according to UNHCR officials.
</P>
<P>
UNHCR officials said the refugees volunteered to go back to
their country after their government accepted them.
</P>
<P>
Prior to departure they were inoculated against yellow fever,
supplied with tents, given 60 U.S. dollars each and food rations
to last three months.
</P>
<P>
The refugees are victims of the 1977 border war between
Ethiopia and Somalia in 1977. They took refuge in Somalia which
lost the war but ran into Kenya in 1991 when Somalia lapsed into
anarchy after the collapse of the central government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
