<HEADLINE> Brazil Beats New Zealand for Conferations Cup Semifinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Marcos Paulo and Ronaldinho
scored two goals in each half to pace Brazil for its third
straight win over New Zealand, securing its top spot in the group
and booking its semifinal berth in the Confederations Cup in
Guadalajara Friday evening.
</P>
<P>
Paulo made an unexpected shot from afar in the injury time of
the first half, beating goalkeeper Michael Utting aghast, while
Ronaldinho fired a free kick to the right of the goal in the 87th
minute.
</P>
<P>
After the all the preliminary matches concluded, Brazil that
booked its semifinal berth even before the game, will play Saudi
Arabia in a Sunday semifinal while Mexico plays the United States
that eliminated Germany 2-0 early today.
</P>
<P>
Brazil fielded in many new starters for the game against New
Zealand that alway kicked out of the tournament prior to the game,
even Ronaldinho who scored in all the three group matches, was
sent in as a second half substitute.
</P>
<P>
New Zealand's defense seemed to crumble in the second half but
they also wasted two great scoring opportunities in a battle
expected to be won by the Brazilians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
