<HEADLINE> Agassi Wins, Michang Chang Loses in Mercedes Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Andre Agassi had an
easy sailing as his opponent surrendered after injury, while
Michael Chang was toppled by a low-ranked Australian in the
quarterfinals of the Mercedez Benz Cup tennis tournament in Los
Angeles on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Agassi led 5-4 in the first set when Lleyton
Hewitt sprained his left ankle and asked to stop the game for
treatment.
</P>
<P>
The 18-year-old Aussie returned to the court to hit a few balls
before he told the umpire he couldn't continue.
</P>
<P>
Agassi thus will face another Aussie Andrew Ilie in the
semifinal, who beat unseeded Frenchman Anthony Dupuis 6-7 (6/8), 6-
4, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Second-seeded Sampras also meets an Aussie in the semifinal, a
qualifier James Sekulov who eliminated Michael Chang 2-6, 6-2, 6-2,
after his victory over South African Wayne Ferreira 4-6, 6-3, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
"By far this is the best I've played against him," said Sampras,
who had lost the last four of five meetings against Ferreira.
</P>
<P>
"Knowing I lost to Wayne four times in a row, I came out pumped
up, almost too much so," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
