<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cambodia to Host ASEAN Ministerial Meeting in 2002 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian Foreign Minister Hor
Nam Hong said Saturday that Cambodia will host the ASEAN
Ministerial Meeting in 2002.
</P>
<P>
Hor Nam Hong made the remarks upon his return from the meeting
of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) in
Singapore.
</P>
<P>
Hor Nam Hong told reporters at the airport that Cambodia was
received a warm welcome at the ASEAN meeting by the other members
of the group and shared views on the current and future prospects
for better regional security, stability and economic prosperity.
</P>
<P>
"During the meetings I also briefed the current situations in
Cambodia and encourage the member countries to come and invest in
Cambodia," he added.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, he announced that Cambodia will host the
ASEAN informal summit in 2002.
</P>
<P>
It was the first time Cambodia attended the 32th ASEAN
Ministerial Meeting, the Sixth ASEAN Regional Forum and the ASEAN
Post Ministerial Conferences as a full ASEAN member since the
country was formally admitted to ASEAN in April.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN Ministerial Meeting, comprising ministers of foreign
affairs of the member states, meets annually in each member
country in turn to formulate policy guidelines and coordinate
ASEAN activities.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN has decided to hold next year's ASEAN Ministerial Meeting
in Thailand. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
