<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Davenport, Williams Advances into Semifinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Second-seeded Venus Williams
beat sixth-seeded Anna Kournikova 6-1, 6-3 in a teenager-
quarterfinal of the Bank of the West Classic in California Friday
evening.
</P>
<P>
The American Williams, ranked fourth in the world, used a
powerful serve and hard ground strokes to beat Russian Kornikova,
ranked 13th in the world, for the fourth straight time.
</P>
<P>
"I believe when anyone tries to hit with me, that's when you're
going to lose," said the 18-year-old Williams who enjoyed a 36-6
record this year.
</P>
<P>
After Kournikova broke serve to tie the second set at 3-3,
Williams kept winning all the way to seal the competition in
merely 67 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Williams thus will play fourth-seeded Amanda Coetzer, who
rallied for a 2-6, 7-5, 6-2 victory over eighth-seeded Sandrine
Testud.
</P>
<P>
Lindsay Davenport recorded another remarkable win of 6-3, 6-3
over Cornia Morariu and will play her semifinal opponent Amy
Frazier who advanced with a 7-5, 6-0 victory over Luxembourg's
Anne Kremer.
</P>
<P>
Davenport, the world's top-ranked player, recorded four aces in
the same game. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
