<TEXT>
<P>
DPPC Commissioner Simon Mechale and Canadian ambassador to
Ethiopia John Schram signed the agreement respectively. (Ethiopia-
Canadian Aid)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NAIROBI -- Ashanti Goldfields Company (AGC) Group, one of the
leading gold producers in the world, lost approximately 63,000
ounces of gold at the Obuasi mine during the industrial action by
workers last May, an AGC report said Friday.
</P>
<P>
However, operations have normalized and officials of the
company said production levels are set to improve gradually,
saying "about half of the Obuasi production shortfall was offset
by 30,000 ounces better than the forecast production at the
Bibiani, Siguiri and Iduapriem mines," all owned by Ashanti. (
Ghana-Gold Production)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- The 11-nation euro zone has registered a trade
surplus with the rest of the world in May this year, Eurostat
reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The statistical bureau of the European community said that the
euro zone chalked up a trade surplus of 2.7 billion euro (2.8
billion U.S. dollars) compared with 5.4 billion euro (5.67 billion
U.S. dollars) in the previous month. (Euro Zone-Trade-Surplus)
</P>
