<DOCNO> XIE19990731.0165 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Argentina Hails Trade Agreement With Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Argentine politicians hailed
the agreement reached Friday with Brazil to restore the bilateral
trade relations, terming it as a good news for the regional
Mercosure trade bloc.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was reached early Friday morning in Brazil by
Argentine President Carlos Menem and his Brazilian counterpart
Fernando Henrique Cardoso.
</P>
<P>
Interior Minister Carlos Corach said the agreement saved the
Southern Common Market (Mercosur), which is comprised of Brazil,
Argentina, Paraguay and Uruguay, with Bolivia and Chile as
associate members.
</P>
<P>
Describing the accord as a good one, General-secretary of the
Presidential Palace Alberto Kohan said now Mercosur can forge
ahead again.
</P>
<P>
Fernando de la Rua, a leader of the country's opposition
alliance, also expressed his satisfaction with the agreement,
which aims at clearing the trade conflicts between Argentina and
Brazil within Mercosur.
</P>
<P>
De la Rua said that the economic bloc "must be for the good of
everybody and not to destroy any one."
</P>
<P>
Relations between Argentina and Brazil grew tense after Buenos
Aires announced in July restrictions over the flooding imports
from Brazil, involving textile and steel products, electric
appliances, paper and shoes. Brazil, in response, broke off all
trade talks.
</P>
<P>
During their Friday meeting, the two presidents also decided to
discuss ways in Montevideo, Uruguay, next Wednesday to settle the
remaining trade problems and promote the bilateral trade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
