<HEADLINE> 5 Killed, 31 Injured in Traffic Accident in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Five people were killed and 31
others injured Friday in a traffic accident in Western province of
Sri Lanka, police sources here said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
At least five dead and 31 others injured when a luxury bus
proceeding from Colombo to Elpitiya collided head-on with another
bus coming from Matugama to Colombo, at Nagashandiya, over 50 from
Colombo, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The injured passengers were admitted to Nagoda hospital. Some
of them were in serious condition, the sources said, adding that
the cause of the accident is still under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
