<HEADLINE> Highlights of Diplomatic News Weekly (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The following are the highlights
of major diplomatic news released by Xinhua in the week.
</P>
<P>
President Meets With WFP Executive Director
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin, in a meeting Friday with executive
director of the World Food Program Catherine Bertini, spoke highly
of WFP's efforts to provide grain aid to developing countries in
the past.
</P>
<P>
He discussed China's program to lift people out of poverty and
expressed his appreciation for WFP's cooperation with China. He
also thanked the WFP for its emergency aid to 4 Chinese provinces
along the Yangtze River that were hit by floods last year and said
he hopes that the cooperation with the WFP can be reinforced to
eradicate poverty in China.
</P>
<P>
 China, U.S. Reach Agreement on Compensations for Embassy
Bombing Casualties
</P>
<P>
The Chinese and U.S. delegations Friday reached an agreement on
the compensations for the personnel casualties and property losses
caused by the U.S. bombing of the Chinese embassy in Yugoslavia
on May 8 this year, according to the Chinese Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. side will soon pay a compensation fund of 4.5 million
U.S. dollars to the Chinese government, which will distribute the
fund to the family members of the three revolutionary martyrs and
the injured during the bombing.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese and U.S. sides will continue negotiations about the
compensation for the property losses of the Chinese side.
</P>
<P>
U.S. Urged to Settle Permanent NTR with China
</P>
<P>
China has demanded that the United States settle its permanent
Normal Trading Relations (NTR) issue with China at an early date
in accordance with the trend of times.
</P>
<P>
This will create favorable conditions for the continuous
development of Sino-U.S. economic and trade ties, Foreign Ministry
spokesman Zhu Bangzao said here Wednesday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
