<HEADLINE> Highlights of Diplomatic News Weekly (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Chinese government has all along attached great importance
to the improvement and development of Sino-U.S. relations, a
senior Chinese trade official said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Sun Zhenyu, vice-minister of foreign trade and economic
cooperation, told U.S. Deputy Secretary of Commerce David Aaron
that keeping sound and stable ties between the two countries
accords with the common interests of both, and is conducive to
world peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
 Chinese Defense Minister Meets Brazilian Army Commander
</P>
<P>
Defense Minister Chi Haotian reiterated China's principled
stand on the Taiwan issue in a meeting here Monday with Brazilian
Army Commander Gleuber Vieira.
</P>
<P>
"The promotion of the peaceful reunification of China is the
common desire of the Chinese nation and is also an inevitable
historical outcome," Chi said.
</P>
<P>
Chi added, "the Chinese People's Liberation Army, with the task
of maintaining China's sovereignty and territorial integrity, is
ready at any moment to smash any attempts to separate China."
</P>
<P>
 Chinese Defense Minister Meets Malaysian Army Commander
</P>
<P>
Defense Minister Chi Haotiao, in a meeting with Malaysian Army
Commander Mohd Hashim Hussein on Monday, said that the two
countries have kept frequent state-to-state and military-to-
military mutual visits since the establishment of diplomatic ties.
</P>
