<HEADLINE> Vietnam Treasures Friendship with ROK: FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, July 31 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam continues to treasure its
friendship and cooperation with the Republic of Korea (ROK), said
Vietnam's Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign Minister Nguyen Manh
Cam during his talks Friday with visiting ROK Minister of Foreign
Affairs and Trade Hong Soon Young.
</P>
<P>
Hong Soon Young is on an official visit to Vietnam from July 28
to July 31 at the invitation of his Vietnamese counterpart Nguyen
Manh Cam.
</P>
<P>
During the talks with Hong Soon Young, Cam asked the ROK to
cooperate with Vietnam to speed up the implementation of

high-level bilateral agreements reached last December regarding
the Economic Development Cooperation Fund (EDCF) loans,
non-refundable aid, increase of investment and labor cooperation,
education, training and exchange of youths' visits.
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed to soon sign the supplemented EDCF
preferential loans for Vietnam's Thien Tan Water Supply Plant (7.3
million U.S. dollars) and Ba Ria Power Plant (7.1 million dollars)
and disburse an EDCF loan for a vaccine-producing project.
</P>
<P>
They also agreed on early signing an agreement for a
second-phase non-refundable aid of 400,000 dollars to help Vietnam
build a stock exchange.
</P>
<P>
The ROK, Hong Soon Young said, will pay attention to Vietnam's
request for developing a new urban area in Hanoi, facilitating
Vietnamese exports to the ROK and recruiting more Vietnamese
workers as the ROK's economy is recovering.
</P>
<P>
Cam and Hong Soon Young also informed each other of their
respective countries' situation and exchanged views on
international and regional issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Vietnamese President Tran Duc Luong and Prime Minister Phan Van
Khai received Hong Soon Young in Hanoi on Friday on separate
occasions.
</P>
</TEXT>
