<HEADLINE> More Tourists Visit Portugal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Nine million people visited
Portugal in the first five months of this year, a 5.3 percent
increase over the same period in 1998, according to the latest
official data.
</P>
<P>
The tourism industry earned 1.14 billion U.S. dollars during
the period, registering a 3.7 percent increase, said a report from
the General Tourism Direction published Friday by a local
newspaper.
</P>
<P>
The average hotel room occupancy rate was 45.1 percent, three
percentage points up from the corresponding period last year.
</P>
<P>
The tourism authority attributed the good performance of the
industry to the image campaign the country has been promoting
since last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
