<HEADLINE> 23 Rebel Suspects Arrested by Sri Lankan police </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 31 (Xinhua) -- At least 23 Tamil rebel suspects
have been taken into custody by Sri Lankan police for questioning
here since the suicide bomb attack on Neelan Thiruchelvam on
Thursday, police said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The suspects were rounded up in different parts of Colombo as
the police and armed forces tightened security with road blocks,
police patrols and searches, police sources said.
</P>
<P>
Thiruchelvam, vice-president of the Tamil United Liberation
Front and a parliamentarian, was killed instantly Thursday morning
in a suicide bombing attack at a stone's throw from his home in
Colombo.
</P>
<P>
The bomber jumped off the back of a motorcyclist and onto his
car as it approached a busy intersection.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the move followed reports that several members
of a group of rebel suicide members sent to Colombo by the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) to attack people in their
hit list were still at large.
</P>
<P>
They said those in the rebel hit list include several
government ministers, Tamil politicians and defense officers.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a civil war against the government
for a separate Tamil state in the north and east of the country
since 1983. 
</P>
</TEXT>
