<DATE_TIME> 1999-07-31 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cuban Scientists Succeed in Vitiligo Test in Monkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- A team of Cuban researchers
succeeded, for the first time in history, to cause the symptoms of
vitiligo to appear in a primate to which they had administered the
plasma of patients afflicted with that ailment, announced a Cuban
scientist.
</P>
<P>
Vitiligo patients' blood plasma contains a substance that
interferes with the normal process of pigmentation in the fur of
an African green monkey, Professor Carlos Miyares Cao, was quoted
by the official newspaper Gramma as saying.
</P>
<P>
Miyares Cao, who discovered a substance extracted from human
placentas and used it for the treatment of vitiligo, directed the
experiment at the Placentary Histotherapy Center in Havana.
</P>
<P>
The loss of pigment in the primate's fur started 17 days after
it received the first doses of plasma; the first symptoms showed
in its face and abdomen and -- almost simultaneously -- in the
limbs.
</P>
<P>
Vitiligo is an ailment that causes the loss of pigment in the
skin of the patients, mainly in the face and the hands.
</P>
<P>
At the beginning of this decade, the Placentary Histotherapy
Center researchers, for the first time, made their tests in black
mice, with which they obtained a biological model to cause
vitiligo in animals.
</P>
<P>
The scientists separated the plasma into fractions of high and
low molecular weight, and they confirmed that the former is the
one that causes the loss of pigment.
</P>
<P>
According to clinical studies, 70 percent of the patients said
they suffered an emotional shock as the detonator of the ailment.
</P>
<P>
Theories about the start of vitiligo say that the malady has
neurogenic (of nervous origin), autocytotoxic (because of toxic
activity provoked by the melanocite itself), and auto-immune
causes, according to the experts.
</P>
<P>
About 120 million to 180 million people in the world, almost
three percent of the total population, suffer this ailment.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
