<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Crude Price Surges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Venezuela's crude oil price rose
by 30 cents on Friday to 17.40 dollars per barrel, according to
the Ministry of Energy and Mines (MEM).
</P>
<P>
MEM's news release said the annual average crude price has
reached 12.58 dollars per barrel, higher than the pre-predicted
price of 9.00 dollars a barrel envisaged by the country and the
state petroleum company (PDVSA).
</P>
<P>
Venezuela's average crude price stood at 10.57 dollars per
barrel in 1998 and 16.32 dollars in 1997. 
</P>
