<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Beats Germany for Confederations Cup Semi Berth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Ben Olsen and Joe-Max Moore
scored goals to lead the United States past Germany into the
semifinals of the Confederations Cup soccer tournament Friday
evening.
</P>
<P>
Olsen opened the scoring for the United States in the 23rd
minute when he took a pass from Morosely Balboa and shot it to the
left of goalkeeper Jens Lehmann. In the 49th minute, Moore made it
2-0 by driving a free kick into the top right corner of the goal.
</P>
<P>
The Americans mounted a strong defense in the penalty box, and
Balboa repeatedly cleared the ball during German offensives.
</P>
<P>
The United States showed surprising strength against Germany,
traditionally one of the world's best teams.
</P>
<P>
The Americans defeated the Germans 3-0 in February in Florida,
and many had said another loss to the Americans would be
humiliating.
</P>
<P>
In the last group match, Brazil leads New Zealand 1-0 by
scoring the goal in the injury time of the first half.
</P>
<P>
Brazil would almost undoubtedly finish first in group B, which
would allow it face Saudi Arabia in a semifinal game on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Americans will play Sunday's semifinal against Mexico.
</P>
</TEXT>
