<HEADLINE> Kafelnikov Books Semi Berth in Generali Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Yevgeny Kafelnikov
recorded his three-set victory to seure a semifinal berth in the
Generali Open tennis tournament in Kitzbuehel, Austria on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Against unseeded Richard Fromberg, Kafelnikov, who failed to
win a tournament since his brief stint atop the world rankings in
the spring, rallied from a loss in the tiebreaker to beat the
Australian 6-3, 6-7 (6-8) and 6-3.
</P>
<P>
The Russian advanced to the semifinals on Saturday against
fifth seed Alberto Costa of Spain, the defending champion, who
defeated countryman Juan Carlos Ferrero, 3-6, 6-2, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
In later matches, 13th seed Fernando Vicente of Spain defeated
No. 6 Nicolas Lapentti of Ecuador 6-7 (4-7), 6-1, 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Vicente thus will face Stefan Koubek, the 15th seed Austrian
who gave another boost to the home crowd with a mild upset over
seventh seed Fernando Meligeni of Brazil 6-2, 6-3. 
</P>
</TEXT>
