<HEADLINE> Nine Killed, Dozens Injured in Bomb Blast in Colombia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, July 30 (Xinhua) -- A car bomb detonated
Friday in the Colombian city of Medellin leaving at least nine
people dead and 30 injured.
</P>
<P>
The explosion occurred at 15:15 (local time) outside the
headquarters of the Rural Anti-Kidnapping Group, said Metropolitan
Police chief Luis Alfredo Rodriguez. Six houses and 20 vehicles
were also destroyed.
</P>
<P>
Rodriguez said the perpetrators of the terrorist attack and the
quantity or nature of the explosives have not been determined yet.
</P>
<P>
The blast occurred hours before the start of the traditional
Flowers Fair, which attracts a great number of national and
foreign tourists, and near the "Atanasio Girardot" stadium, where
a concert to officially inaugurate the event had been announced.
</P>
