<HEADLINE> Venezuelan Commercial Aircraft Missing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, July 30 (Xinhua) -- A Venezuelan commercial light
airplane went missing Friday morning and authorities suspected it
was hijacked by Colombian guerrillas, local media reported.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft, taking off Friday morning from the Simon Bolivar
Airport in Maiquetia, lost contact with the control tower at 09:45
local time (1345 GMT) while it was about 32 kilometers from the
Guasdalito Airport, its intended destination, which is located 650
kilometers southwest of Caracas.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the disappearance is under investigation. Local
authorities suspect a hijack because the aircraft disappeared in
the paramilitary border areas where Colombian guerrillas are
active.
</P>
<P>
The number of people aboard is not clear. A civilian transit
director said there were 16 persons aboard, including two pilots,
while a local television network said 21 persons were missing.
</P>
<P>
The Venezuelan Air Force and National Guard helicopters are
combing the area for the missing plane. 
</P>
