<HEADLINE> Anelka "Will not Play for Arsenal Again" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 30 (Xinhua) -- English football club Arsenal
manager Arsene Wenger said he is convinced that want-away striker
Nicolas Anelka has played his last game for the club.
</P>
<P>
Anelka has been ordered to return to Highbury after his 23
million pounds transfer to Lazio fell through over the Frenchman's
failure to reach personal terms with the Italian club.
</P>
<P>
But Wenger was in defiant mood on Friday and insisted the 20-
year-old frontman was no longer welcome in his team.
</P>
<P>
"What is 99% sure now is that he will not play for us any more,
" Wenger said.
</P>
<P>
"What is important at the moment is the club and my team - not
Nicolas Anelka any more, because he cannot fight for us."
</P>
<P>
"It is more important for me to make 250,000 people happy than
one - that's my target."
</P>
<P>
"I think we have a strong team, we have a strong squad and we
are determined to do well in Europe and in England."
</P>
<P>
"We lost a very good player, but that happens to every club,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
The Arsenal boss believes the farce over Anelka's non-movement
indicates that there is an urgent need to reform the international
transfer system.
</P>
<P>
Anelka's two brothers, who act as the player's advisers, have
been criticized for their roles in the deal and their massive wage
demands.
</P>
<P>
"It's not only the behavior of Anelka that's a little bit
surprising," Wenger said.
</P>
<P>
"I believe that the whole transfer system has to be rescheduled
and changed. FIFA has a lot of work to do."
</P>
<P>
"I was closely involved in that deal, and there are some
surprising things going on at the moment in the transfer market."
</P>
<P>
"Perhaps FIFA has lost control and the rules are not respected
any more," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
