nailed down his country first gold in the 13th Pan Am Games,
recording six 10s for a cumulative of 99.6 points, 1.4 points
ahead of second-placed American Armando Ayala.
</P>
<P>
The United States, most of whose shooters are in the military
and are paid to train full-time, bagged home nine of 14 golds on
offer at the Pan Am shooting events. 
