<HEADLINE> Qingdao Beer Group Expands Business into Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, July 31 (Xinhua) -- The Qingdao Beer Group, the largest
beer producer in China, today merged the Huangshi City Beer
Factory in Hubei Province, expanding its business into central
China.
</P>
<P>
The newly established company is called the Qingdao (Huangshi)
Beer Company. The Huangshi City Beer Factory had been developing
slowly due to a lack of capital.
</P>
<P>
Li Guirong, chairman of the board of directors of the Dingdao
Beer Group, said they intend to increase the factory's annual
output to 80,000 tons within the next few years from the present
45,000 tons by introducing new technology and processing
techniques.
</P>
<P>
Li said the group, set up as early as 1903 in east China's
Shandong Province, has its products on the market in over 40
countries and regions, and is the best-known Chinese brand in the
world. The company annually exports about 400,000 standard cartons
of beer, and has now set up 17 beer breweries throughout China,
with domestic market-share and exports both number one in the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
